docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Monday fanned expectations for his meeting with Kim Jong-un, saying he would like his talks with the North Korean leader to take place at the Demilitarized Zone that separates the two Koreas because “there’s a great celebration to be had on the site” if the negotiations are successful.

headline.main: Trump, Hoping for ‘Great Celebration,’ Wants to Hold North Korea Talks in DMZ
headline.print_headline: Trump Wants Talks With North Korea in DMZ, a Cold War Holdover

docs.abstract: For Democratic women, no endorsement is as powerful as one from the fund-raising juggernaut. But with so many female candidates, the group is forced to pick between them.
docs.snippet: For Democratic women, no endorsement is as powerful as one from the fund-raising juggernaut. But with so many female candidates, the group is forced to pick between them.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the night before she announced her candidacy for governor, Stacey Evans got a telephone call from Emily’s List, the fund-raising juggernaut that has helped elect hundreds of Democratic women who support abortion rights. It was not a happy conversation.

headline.main: Tough Choices, and Criticism, for Emily’s List as Democratic Women Flood Primaries
headline.print_headline: PAC Aiding Female Democrats Faces Tough Calls as More Run
